# Wantlist Tracker — Project Context (v0.9.0, 2026-03-22)

## What it is
A single-page web app that checks a user's music wantlist/collection against record stores in Porto and Lisbon, Portugal. Live at: https://j-dealmeida.github.io/Discogs-Wantlist-Tracker/

## Architecture
- **Frontend**: Single `index.html` (vanilla JS, no framework, no build step)
- **Backend**: Cloudflare Worker (`worker/index.js`) that acts as CORS proxy + cache layer
- **Hosting**: GitHub Pages (main branch auto-deploys)
- **KV cache**: Cloudflare KV namespace (`INVENTORY_KV`) for Shopify catalogs and Discogs seller inventories

## Data sources (user can load from any, or merge multiple)
1. **Discogs wantlist** — fetched via worker proxy using release ID (most accurate)
2. **MusicBrainz collection** — public collections, matched by title search
3. **File import** — Discogs CSV export, iTunes XML library, iTunes playlist TSV

